<br>
As for the aggro, the damage output of the Frostbringer will be superior having both more damage and faster delay.  Also, I believe the Veno Axe is a DD + DoT (poison) iirc.  The Frostbringer is a DD + AC debuff on the mob.  Debuffs are very high aggro and DoT's are not.  Tash is a huge aggro spell for chanters and does no damage where my druid has a 900ish point DoT and gets very little aggro from it.  Slow is another example of a debuff that draws aggro yet causes no damage.<br>
<br>
The Frostbringer is one of the most affordable decent aggro weapons available to the common warrior IMO that still does respectable damage.  At your level I would toy around with it in your onhand if your other option is a Lamentation or Defiance.  To me 9/19 weapons aren't what they are cracked up to be.  They used to be top of the line weapons but that era has passed.  There are too many weapons now with damage/delay ratios greater than 0.5.  I would consider something like a Jarseth Trident (11/22) offhand until your main hand damage bonus gets large enough to utilize lower delay weapons and then switch Frostbringer to offhand.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
<br>
